videos.title: I Ran a BRUTAL Ultra Marathon in Mongolia (155 Miles, 30-Pound Pack)
videos.description:
Racing the Gobi March in Mongolia was one of the toughest physical challenges I've ever taken on. See how it turned out, and whether I managed to achieve the place on the podium that I had dreamt of.

Thank you to the Racing the Planet team for putting on such an incredible event, and capturing it on video - I couldn't have made this film without their help. Mary, Andrei, Onni - you guys rock. A massive thank you to all the volunteers and organizers who came together to make this race possible. And of course, CONGRATS to every single person who ran the race. It was such a pleasure meeting you all.

Here is Racing the Planet's website, where you can see some of the inspiring races they organize around the globe: https://racingtheplanet.com

videos.title: This Is THE Dream Adventure Car (I Got to Drive it Before It Was Released)
videos.description:
This video was created in partnership with Toyota for the launch of the new Toyota Land Cruiser. Here is the final, official 30-second TV ad üé•üí• https://youtu.be/tUl43BeD5mY
For more information, go to your local Toyota website!

In January, I travelled to Morocco to film the campaign for the launch of the much-awaited Toyota Land Cruiser 2024. It felt truly surreal to see this car before it hit the roads - we were driving an actual prototype down the endless trails and into the Sahara desert of Morocco! So wild.

This film would not have been possible without the hard work of an incredible, international production team. Adi, Hugo, Alex, Nathalie, Gador, Sergio, Tom, Nouredinne, Yousef, Anke, Mihaela, Laurin,  and everyone else - THANK YOU. You were an absolute dream team and I'm so grateful to have met all of you. May our wild paths cross again someday!

Also, here is a 10-minute version of the official Toyota ad, in case you can't get enough üòÖ : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D48lcBqcuvo

videos.title: I Spent 48 Hours with Reindeer Herders in Norway
videos.description:
You can visit Nils and his family via the wonderful Visit Natives (https://www.visitnatives.com/ ), who are one of the few truly sustainable travel businesses in the industry. For Nils, welcoming travellers is just a side hustle he does in addition to herding his reindeer, and Visit Natives helps him coordinate who comes and when. I absolutely love what they do, so definitely check them out.

Over on my Patreon, you'll soon find some more exclusive footage from this experience that didn't make it to the final cut of this YouTube video! Come join the adventure community here: https://patreon.com/evazubeck

videos.title: I Didn't Want to Quit.
videos.description:
Thank you to the incredible Montane Arctic Lapland Ultra (https://lapland.arcticultra.de/) for having Vilk and I join your 185km distance. I can't wait to come back for a redemption run.

Thank you to Callum Jolliffe for the drone shots and the footage from the checkpoints, and David Dougan for additional videography. And a big thanks to Racelite, co-sponsors of the race who specialize in all things trail running and Arctic running: https://www.racelite.de/

Here is the Q&A video if you'd like to learn more about my and Vilk's training, prep and gear: https://www.patreon.com/posts/q-lapland-arctic-100792949 (it's free and you don't have to sign up to anything, just click on the link)

videos.title: Alone in a Remote Cabin in Northern Sweden (No Road Access)
videos.description:
When I found out that there's a remote cabin near to where I'd been staying in the Arctic Circle, I couldn't resist a hike there. Several hours through the frozen wild lands of northern Sweden, I finally got there, and what I found really surprised me.

P.S. You can stay in this cabin too! If you'd like to stay in this cabin or at the more accessible cabins of Vuoggatjalme, get in touch with Frans on https://vuoggatjalme.se/

Vilk flew in the 48" collapsible Impact Crate, paired with IATA brackets and the wheel cart.

videos.title: LIVE: YSL RICO Trial ‚Äî GA v. Deamonte Kendrick and Shannon Stillwell ‚Äî Day 165
videos.description:
Atlanta rapper Young Thug, born Jeffery Williams, and many of his associates faced multiple charges under Georgia's RICO Act. Williams, believed to be the leader of the YSL collective, pleaded guilty and nolo to multiple charges on October 31 before going home on time served. Many of Thug's other co-defendants took plea deals. However, Shannon Stillwell and Deamonte Kendrick have not taken a plea deal and will continue in the RICO trial. Both face racketeering conspiracy charges alleging they participated in criminal street gang activity, along with drug and gun violations.
